**NEWSLETTER PROCESS FLOW SOP DOCUMENTATION**

**Summary Overview of the System**

This system uses Make.com to automate the entire newsletter process, pulling content from sources like Inoreader RSS, LinkedIn, Reddit, and Google Sheets. AI curates and summarizes the latest news, trending posts, and AI tool updates, tailoring everything to the target audience using market data from Google Docs. The workflows filter and organize only the most relevant content into an engaging, ready-to-send newsletter.

After the content is compiled, automation takes care of formatting, testing, and sending it out through Brevo. With daily schedules and smart triggers in Google Sheets, the whole process—from gathering news to email delivery—runs smoothly with minimal manual effort. This ensures each newsletter is consistent, high quality, and perfectly targeted.

---

**Important Notes:**

* This automation is using GoogleApps script in the Google sheet to trigger the webhooks in make.com. The Apps script code is in a different document.

---

**Tech Stack:**

* Make.com \- automations platform  
* Google Sheet \- database and front-end UI  
* Inoreader RSS Feed \- for daily updated news articles  
* ChatGPT/Claude \- for content creation  
* ChatGPT/Perplexity \- for researching  
* Apify \- for scraping  
* Brevo \- for sending the newsletter email campaign

---

**How it Works: End-to-End Flow (Front-End)**

* 1st step: Make automations triggers daily and send content to google sheet.  
* 2nd step: User reviews the contents in different sheets (sections of the article) and puts a checkmark on the ones that passed the qualification (“Include in Newsletter?” columns).  
* 3rd step: User goes to the “Social Media Posts” sheet and clicks the “Yes” button on column G (“Trigger the content making automation”) to create the whole newsletter via a google document.  
* 4th step: User goes to the “Newsletter Drafts” sheet and double checks the google document if the newsletter content is okay.  
* 5th step: User goes to the “Newsletter Drafts” sheet and clicks the “Yes” button on column C (“Final and push a test email?”) to send a test email to his/her own email.  
* 6th step: If everything is already good, user clicks the “Yes” button on column E (“Send final newsletter to Brevo”) to send the newsletter campaign to the email list.

---

**Make.com Automations Step By Step Process (Back-End)**  


1.) **INOREADER RSS**: Trigger Daily 9am \-\> Select Top 3 \-\> Create Content \-\> Put GoogleSheet

* 1st step: Get the list of news articles summary daily from Inoreader RSS feed. Filters news articles that only have a summary.  
* 2nd step: Aggregates all data into one bundle.  
* 3rd step: Get the “Target Market” Definition from a google document to be added to the AI model in the next step.  
* 4th step: ChatGPT chooses top 3 articles based on Target Market definition.  
  * **Prompt**:  
    \#SYSTEM  
    You are a helpful intelligent writing assistant that helps me SELECT THE TOP 3 ARTICLES to post for my newsletter.  
      
    I will also add my persona and preferences below for more context.  
      
    Persona:  
    {{PERSONA DYNAMIC VARIABLE TEXT IS HERE}}  
      
    End of Persona Here  
      
    \===============  
      
    \#\#INSTRUCTIONS  
    \-Your task is to select the Top 3 articles based on the Title & Summary provided below. The data provided are separated via \*\*\*\*\*  
      
    \-Choose the top 3 articles from DIFFERENT sources, do not pick from the same source.  
      
    \-Also provide a 50 word expert commentary on why this matters.  
      
    \-Make the source all capital letters.  
      
    \===============  
      
    \#\# BATCH INPUT DATA:  
    {{3.text}}  
      
    \===============  
      
    \#\#FINAL OUTPUT:  
    The final output should be in JSON format array like this:  
      
    {  
      "result": \[  
        {  
          "title": "put the top 1 title here in all capital letters",    
          "expertCommentary": "put your commentary here for top 1",  
          "websiteLink": "put the website citaion link for top 1 here",   
          "imageURL": "put the image URL here if available for top 1",   
          "publicationDate": "put the publication date for top 1 here",   
          "source": "extract the main source here for top 1 in all capital letters",   
          "articleSummary": "put the article summary here for top 1"  
        },  
        {  
          "title": "put the top 2 title here in all capital letters",  
          "expertCommentary": "put your commentary here for top 2",   
         "websiteLink": "put the website citaion link for top 2 here",   
          "imageURL": "put the image URL here if available for top 2",   
          "publicationDate": "put the publication date for top 2 here",   
          "source: "extract the main source here for top 2 in all capital letters",   
          "articleSummary": "put the article summary here for top 2"  
        }  
      \]  
    }  
      
    \#\#RULES:  
    \-do not make the title all capital letters  
      
* 5th step: Iterates results coming from the AI model to process one by one.  
* 6th step: Get business photos from Unsplash to be used if the news article doesn’t have its own image.  
* 7th step: Switch module to change image to unsplash image if inoreader image is empty.  
* 8th step: Finds and filters duplicate news articles via link.  
* 9th step: Perplexity searches the link to create a comprehensive summary and relevance angle.  
* 10th step: ChatGPT formats the result to JSON.  
* 11th step: Get the Persona from a google document to be used in the next AI model step.  
* 12th step: Claude creates the news blurb section.  
  * **Prompt**:  
    \# SYSTEM  
    You are a Corporate Treasury expert tasked with crafting a concise newsletter section.  
      
    Do not include any \* or special characters on your final output.  
      
    My persona:  
    {{Dynamic Variable Persona here from Google Doc}}  
      
    END OF PERSONA  
      
    \================  
      
    \#\# INSTRUCTIONS:  
      
    You are a Corporate Treasury expert tasked with crafting a concise newsletter section.  
    Using the provided title, expert commentary, and summary, write a short section consisting of two parts:  
      
    A brief summary of the news or topic (around 15 words), and   
    A thoughtful commentary (making up the remainder of the 50-word limit) explaining how this development relates to corporate finance and treasury, or what it means for corporate treasurers.  
      
    The content should be clear, engaging, and insightful—tailored to Treasury and Finance professionals seeking quick, actionable takeaways.  
      
    \================  
      
    \#\# RULES:  
    \- do not output anything but the text content  
    \- the final output should only be 1 paragraph without newlines.  
    \- do not include any \* or special characters on your final output  
      
    INPUT DATA:   
      
    Title: {{title of the article}}  
      
    Summary: {{summary coming from perplexity}}  
      
    Relevance: {{summary coming from perplexity}}  
      
* 13th step: Add all the relevant data to “Filtered Articles” sheet.

2.) **CONTENT AGGREGATOR**: Trigger from Social Media \-\> Create Content Document \-\> Put GoogleSheets

* 1st step: Get the aggregated news article content subsections from googlesheet and set it as a variable.  
* 2nd step: Get the aggregated AI tools/updates content section from googlesheet and set it as a variable. Mark its status as processed.  
* 3rd step: Get the aggregated social media content section from googlesheet and set it as a variable. Mark its status as processed.  
* 4th step: Get the prompt of the day content from googlesheet and set it as a variable. Mark its status as processed.  
* 5th step: Get the aggregated STS blog post content section from googlesheet and set it as a variable. Mark its status as processed.  
* 6th step: Get the aggregated Upcoming events content section from googlesheet and set it as a variable. Mark its status as processed.  
* 7th step: Get all the aggregated content from variables and feed it to an AI model. Get the persona from a googledoc to add to AI model prompt. AI model creates the Intro content section.  
* 8th step: Get all the aggregated content from variables and feed it to an AI model. Get the persona from a googledoc to add to AI model prompt. AI model creates the Conclusion content section.  
* 9th step:Get all the aggregated content from variables and feed it to an AI model. Get the persona from a googledoc to add to AI model prompt. AI model creates the Today’s Insights bullet point list content section.  
* 9th step: Create google document with all the content combined.  
* 10th step: Update data in Newsletter Drafts sheet.

3.) **CONTENT FORMATTER**: Trigger "Yes" Send Test Email \-\> Format Content using ChatGPT \-\> Create Brevo Email Campaign

* 1st step: Triggers when “Yes” is clicked in Column C (Finalize and Push Test Email?) of “Newsletter Drafts” sheet.  
* 2nd step: Searches for the row in googlesheet to get the relevant data. The filter used is test email does not have “sent” and column C has “yes”  
* 3rd step: Get the complete content of the newsletter from a Google Document.  
* 4th step: AI model formats the whole content into HTML format (with design).  
* 5th step: Create the email campaign on the Brevo platform and automatically assign the List in brevo as recipients.  
* 6th step: Send a test email of the newsletter to the user’s email.  
* 7th step: Updates status as test email “sent” and adds the Campaign ID in googlesheet.

![][image6]

---

4.) **FINAL SENDER**: Trigger "Yes" Send Newsletter \-\> Send Brevo Newsletter Campaign

* 1st step: Triggers when “Yes” is clicked in Column E (Send Final Newsletter to Brevo) of “Newsletter Drafts” sheet..  
* 2nd step: Searches for the row in googlesheet to get the relevant data. The filter used is sent date does not exist and column E has “yes”.  
* 3rd step: Send the email campaign to the Brevo list.  
* 4th step: Update and add the send date to the “date newsletter sent” column so that it won’t be processed again.

**![][image7]**  
---

5.) **SCRAPE SYSTEM**: Trigger Daily 9am \-\> Scrape Internet \-\> Filter \-\> Put GoogleSheets

* 1st step: Run Apify LinkedIn scraper and get trending posts based on the criteria. The criteria is hardcoded in the Apify node in Make. Aggregates all the posts and feeds it to AI model. AI model will choose the top 3 and add it to the “social media posts” sheet.  
* 2nd step: Run Apify Reddit scraper and get trending posts based on the criteria. The criteria is hardcoded in the Apify node in Make. Aggregates all the posts and feeds it to AI model. AI model will choose the top 3 and add it to the “social media posts” sheet.  
* 3rd step: AI model searches the internet for top 5 AI/Automation tools or updates from last week. Creates a summary and provides the citation link to the article. Add it to the “AI tools and update” sheet.  
* 4th step: AI model searches the internet for top 3 viral AI prompts from last week. Creates a summary and provides the citation link to the article. Add it to the “Prompt of the day” sheet.**![][image8]**

6.) **DAILY INSIGHTS PROCESSOR**: Trigger STS Blog Post \-\> Create Overview \-\> Put GoogleSheet

* 1st step: Triggers when the checkbox is clicked in “STS blog posts” sheet in Column F.  
* 2nd step: Search the spreadsheet for the relevant data.  
* 3rd step: Get the persona from a google doc and add it to AI model prompt.  
* 4th step: AI model creates an overview, title and extracts the publication date.  
* 5th step: Another AI model formats it to JSON so that it can be processed one by one.  
* 6th step: Send all the data and content to the “STS blog posts” sheet.

* 1st step: Triggers when the checkbox is clicked in the “AI tools and updates” sheet in Column E.  
* 2nd step: Search the spreadsheet for the relevant data.  
* 3rd step: Get the persona from a google doc and add it to AI model prompt.  
* 4th step: AI model creates an overview, title and extracts the publication date.  
* 5th step: Another AI model formats it to JSON so that it can be processed one by one.  
* 6th step: Send all the data and content to the “AI tools and updates” sheet.

8.) **UPCOMING EVENTS PROCESSOR**: Trigger Upcoming Events \-\> Create Overview \-\> Put GoogleSheet

* 1st step: Triggers when the checkbox is clicked in the “Upcoming events” sheet in Column F.  
* 2nd step: Search the spreadsheet for the relevant data.  
* 3rd step: Get the persona from a google doc and add it to AI model prompt.  
* 4th step: AI model creates an overview, title and extracts the publication date.  
* 5th step: Another AI model formats it to JSON so that it can be processed one by one.  
* 6th step: Send all the data and content to the “Upcoming events” sheet.

9.) **ARTICLE SEARCH**: Perplexity Search Daily \-\> Claude Create News Subsection Blurb \-\> Put in "Filtered Articles"

* 1st step: Triggers daily at 8am and Perplexity searches the internet for relevant news article.  
  * Prompt:  
    \# SYSTEM  
    You are an expert researching agent.  
      
    \# FINAL OUTPUT FORMAT  
    1\. Article Name  
       \- Summary: summary here  
       \- Relevance: explain the relevance here  
       \- Citation Link: Put the complete citation link here  
       \- Publication Date: put the publication date here  
      
    2\. Article Name  
       \- Summary: summary here  
       \- Relevance: explain the relevance here  
       \- Citation Link: Put the complete citation link here  
       \- Publication Date: put the publication date here  
      
    User Input:  
    Your task is to find the 10 most widely shared and talked about articles published in the last 24 hours on topics that would be of high interest to corporate leaders in corporate finance and corporate treasury regarding finance and treasury transformation, technology, and optimization.  
      
    Prioritize searching the website below:  
    https://www.corporatefinancebrief.com/accounts-payable/treasury/  
    https://treasury-management.com/  
    https://treasuryxl.com/  
    https://www.financialexecutives.org/  
    https://gfmag.com/  
    https://www.thecorporatetreasurer.com/  
    https://www.eurofinance.com/  
    https://www.treasuryandrisk.com/  
    https://the-cfo.io/category/risk-and-economy/  
    https://www.jpmorgan.com/insights/treasury  
    https://www.jpmorgan.com/insights/technology  
    https://www.jpmorgan.com/insights/payments  
    https://www.jpmorgan.com/insights/fraud  
    https://www.workingcapitalforum.com/news  
    https://www.financialprofessionals.org/  
      
* 2nd step: ChatGPT formats the data to JSON.  
* 3rd step: Iterate all the results one by one to loop it.  
* 4th step: ChatGPT decides image keywords based on the Title and Summary.  
* 5th step: Use keywords to search a relevant image in Unsplash.  
* 6th step: Delay 10 secs for rate limiting.  
* 7th step: Find duplicates in googlesheet using website article link and not process it.  
* 8th step: Get the Persona of the user from a google document to feed to Claude.  
* 9th step: Claude creates subsection news content.  
* 10th step: Add all the relevant data to “Filtered Articles” sheet.
